==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alluvial
<hw>Al*lu"vi*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Alluvial soil;
specif., in Australia, gold-bearing alluvial soil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alluvial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Alluvial
<hw>Al*lu"vi*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>alluvial</ets>. See <er>Alluvion</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to,
contained in, or composed of, alluvium; relating to the deposits made by
flowing water; washed away from one place and deposited in another;
<as>as, <ex>alluvial</ex> soil, mud, accumulations,
deposits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alluvion</ent>⟦br⟧
